                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Anarchy V 2.0</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.67)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=25688">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=12441">***** "Ishmael" *******</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=12441&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> New Version of the old Anarchy deck...much more consistent...</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> September 21, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(625)">Quilla</a>(Horn and Goggles)<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(485)">Trug</a>(None)<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(767)">Bria</a>(get any 2 orothe or any 2 arderial depending on what you need)<br>
<br>
<br>
Creatures(16)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(439)">Paralit</a> x3<br>
Rockslide Hyren x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(476)">Ormagon</a> x3<br>
Rayje&#39;s Construct x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(499)">Colossus</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(773)">Crystal <a href="javascript:card_browser(478)">Parmalag</a></a> x2<br>
<br>
Relics(13)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(652)">Rayje&#39;s Belt</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(529)">Abwyn&#39;s Quill</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(456)">Orothean Goggles</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(785}<a href="javascript:card_browser({557)">Maelstrom</a> Flask</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(348)">Cloud Sceptre</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(629)">Orothean Horn</a> x3<br>
<br>
Spells(11)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(422)">Flood of Energy</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(670}<a href="javascript:card_browser({528)">Sorreah</a>&#39;s Dream</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(647)">Impact</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(498)">Thunderquake</a> x2<br>
<br>
<br>
43 cards, including 3 magi   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont">    Quilla Strategy, is to get the 2 orothe relics, and then try and get a big creature for free through the horn.  If a creature will not come for free then do not put the horn down, save it for later.  Instead play a creature out of your hand.  With Quilla starting the 2 relics, being a 14/7, she will be able to take full advantage of all of the cards in the deck, with the obvious exception of the ardedrial relics.<br>
<br>
   Trug, play a paralit or flood then cataclysm...he has to be my favorite magi.  The Flasks allow you to search for the neccessary boom making device aka flood.<br>
<br>
   Bria is a pain in the a** to kill with the correct setup.  The cards that are key to bria are the 2 orothe and 2 arderial relics...so obviously when she is flipped, you should choose arderial as the region that she may play.  The goal is to cycle through and get the cards that you need for a flip kill.  Use the goggles to get a free big creature on top of the deck, preferably an Ormagon.  Once you play the creature for free, impacting the creature is neccessary, if it is an ormagon then blow it up with a dream and thats game...for those annoying underneath type decks the quill has been added in order to remove the underneath creatures and allow victory.  Otherwise keep the deck cycling with the sceptre and the goggles so that you can get the cards that you need.  Impacting big creatures, blowing up hyrens, t-quaking, and attacking with large creatures while cycling will either kill or severely weaken an opponent while you get the cards that you need.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=25688"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25688" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
